rComments: Professor Pennington was one of the nicest professors I've had so far. He's really passionate about the topic and is a great lecturer. If you attend all the lectures you'll be good without the books. He's not a crazy hard marker and is actually very fair. Definitely recommend taking a course with him!

I tend to only leave ratings if I had a very bad experiences or a very good experiences with a prof. Chris definitely falls into the latter category. He inspires you to study history, has a lot of funny anecdotes throughout his presentations, marks the essays himself providing ample feedback, and loves what he does. I would definitely recommend.
Hardest marker I have ever had. Nice guy, but extremely tough marker. Would not recommend if you want a good mark.

rComments: By far the most amazing professor I have ever had the pleasure of being taught by. His lectures are memorable, infused with own personal stories and he is a prof that remembers what it was like to be a student, lectures are brilliant. I hope to god he teaches more courses in the future because I would love to them.

best prof he explains it extremely well he's very nice and you can tell he cares he's very approachable makes the subject interesting even if you know little of it he's funny too  you need to be there for lectures tests are straighforward book not needed  I actually checked if he teaches anything else during the term to take that class too

Great, great professor. One of the nicest professors too. He has a great passion for Canadian history and it is very clear that he cares about this stuff. His lectures usually consist of him talking for 2 hours but he makes it so interesting and puts in interesting anecdotes that you forget. I wish he thought more courses at UTM

AMAZING prof! The textbook is useless because the midterm and exam were just based on lecture. He usually teachees at UTSC, but has been teaching at UTM for at least 2 years now. He uses a lot of impersonations which help you remember what he's talking about, and he's very interesting. I would suggest this class for sure!
